Strafford,

Dec., 1897. Trask & a. v. Rochester. Appeal, from a sewer location and assessment of damages made by the city council. Worcester, Gafney Snow, for the plaintiffs. George E. Cochrane, for the defendants. Parsons, J.

The case presents no question of law. The only question of law that might have been raised upon the facts stated is settled in Campbell v. Windham, 63 N. H. 465.

Case discharged.

Clark, J., did not sit: the others concurred.
